user_question: What are the best settings for photographing the Milky Way with a DSLR camera?
final_answer: The best settings for photographing the Milky Way with a DSLR camera typically include a wide aperture (f/2.8 or lower), a high ISO (1600-3200), and a long exposure time (20-30 seconds) using a wide-angle lens.
